I've created a comprehensive SNMP walk application in Python. Here's what the application includes:Features:SNMP Walk: Traverse SNMP trees starting from any OIDSNMP Get: Retrieve single OID valuesMultiple output formats: table, detailed, and simple viewsSNMP version support: v1 and v2cFlexible configuration: custom community strings, ports, timeoutsError handling: Comprehensive error messages and validationRequirements:You'll need to install the pysnmp library:pip install pysnmpUsage Examples:Basic SNMP walk:python snmp_walk.py -t 192.168.1.1Walk with custom community:python snmp_walk.py -t 192.168.1.1 -c privateSingle SNMP GET:python snmp_walk.py -t 192.168.1.1 -g 1.3.6.1.2.1.1.1.0Walk specific OID tree:python snmp_walk.py -t 192.168.1.1 -o 1.3.6.1.2.1.1Key Components:SNMPWalker Class: Handles SNMP operations with proper error handlingCommand-line Interface: Full argument parsing with help and examplesOutput Formatting: Three different display formats for resultsInput Validation: Checks IP addresses and SNMP parametersThe application provides detailed help with --help and includes common OID references. It's designed to be both user-friendly for interactive use and robust enough for scripting purposes.